02:01:04.650 --> 02:01:06.000
He was a strict commander.

1352
02:01:06.200 --> 02:01:07.200
But fair.

1353
02:01:08.910 --> 02:01:10.720
Fair and worth following.

1354
02:01:12.260 --> 02:01:13.260
You loved him.

1355
02:01:14.140 --> 02:01:15.140
As a son.

1356
02:01:17.650 --> 02:01:18.650
Well. he's not dead.

1357
02:01:19.195 --> 02:01:20.740
Will he come home?

1358
02:01:21.860 --> 02:01:22.860
Soon.

1359
02:01:23.420 --> 02:01:24.420
He will bring revenge.

1360
02:01:27.160 --> 02:01:28.160
He will bring everything.

1361
02:01:37.770 --> 02:01:38.770
I will speak.

1362
02:01:38.805 --> 02:01:40.550
We don't want people to find out who you are.

1363
02:01:40.825 --> 02:01:42.625
Well. maybe we shouldn't have taken the guard.

1364
02:01:43.030 --> 02:01:45.070
We'll be glad we took her if
we will have problems on the way.

1365
02:01:57.469 --> 02:01:58.950
I have a link.

1366
02:01:59.710 --> 02:02:00.710
Wait!

1367
02:02:01.630 --> 02:02:03.050
Maybe you sent me.

1368
02:02:05.500 --> 02:02:06.500
Find the beggar.

1369
02:02:22.750 --> 02:02:23.870
Your men must wait outside.

1370
02:02:24.300 --> 02:02:25.300
Weapons too.

1371
02:02:42.390 --> 02:02:43.710
Zeus welcomes you. strangers.

1372
02:02:44.510 --> 02:02:45.510
Have you traveled far?

1373
02:02:46.130 --> 02:02:47.130
Not that far.

1374
02:02:48.660 --> 02:02:50.190
You are here to rest for the night.

1375
02:02:52.640 --> 02:02:54.390
We are here to sacrifice to Athena.

1376
02:02:56.940 --> 02:02:59.590
And any hospitality that
you can offer would be considered.

1377
02:03:00.010 --> 02:03:01.010
Of course.

1378
02:03:01.210 --> 02:03:02.370
Get that beggar out of here.

1379
02:03:02.420 --> 02:03:03.690
He has a message for me.

1380
02:03:05.005 --> 02:03:06.005
Maybe you sent me?

1381
02:03:07.250 --> 02:03:08.250
Yes. sir.

1382
02:03:14.410 --> 02:03:15.410
Well. what's the link?

1383
02:03:17.090 --> 02:03:18.090
It is private.

1384
02:03:18.349 --> 02:03:19.349
These men are a bitch...

1385
02:03:21.230 --> 02:03:22.230
These men are a bitch...

1386
02:03:39.960 --> 02:03:41.780
This is your moment to leave. old man.

1387
02:03:42.620 --> 02:03:43.620
Go. stranger.

1388
02:03:46.340 --> 02:03:48.260
I've already saved one old man this week.

1389
02:03:49.010 --> 02:03:50.010
But he was blind.

1390
02:03:50.810 --> 02:03:51.810
I don't save...

1391
02:04:30.670 --> 02:04:32.090
Not bad for a beggar.

1392
02:04:32.995 --> 02:04:34.090
No one is born a beggar.

1393
02:04:35.050 --> 02:04:37.730
We will take the robe of this priest.
we'll put it on your armor.

1394
02:04:40.230 --> 02:04:41.230
Help me with his body.

1395
02:04:41.510 --> 02:04:42.510
We have to leave him here.

1396
02:04:42.970 --> 02:04:43.370
Nope.

1397
02:04:43.590 --> 02:04:44.650
We have to get out of here.

1398
02:04:45.605 --> 02:04:46.965
This is not how respect is given to the dead.

1399
02:04:47.030 --> 02:04:48.330
This is how to survive.

1400
02:04:48.470 --> 02:04:49.470
He was my teacher.

1401
02:04:51.030 --> 02:04:52.330
Maybe it was Athena in disguise.

1402
02:04:52.331 --> 02:04:53.570
His name was Mentor.

1403
02:04:54.525 --> 02:04:57.130
And when you're safe. we'll release
on a journey to the unknown west.

1404
02:04:57.870 --> 02:04:58.870
And we will honor him there.

1405
02:04:59.430 --> 02:05:00.890
These men were sent by suitors.

1406
02:05:01.550 --> 02:05:03.670
There will be more of them. we have to
set out on a journey.

1407
02:05:03.930 --> 02:05:04.390
At night?

1408
02:05:04.820 --> 02:05:05.850
It's safer than staying here.

1409
02:05:06.429 --> 02:05:08.550
The mentor is in the heart
the oldest temple of Athena.

1410
02:05:09.370 --> 02:05:11.330
For now. we will honor him with a flame.

1411
02:05:50.540 --> 02:05:52.180
So how does the beggar find out about the Mentor?

1412
02:05:52.450 --> 02:05:54.700
I told you. I wasn't always a beggar.

1413
02:05:55.400 --> 02:05:56.600
You have smart eyes.

1414
02:05:57.445 --> 02:05:58.200
Athena's eyes.

1415
02:05:58.220 --> 02:05:59.620
Do not seek gods or men.

1416
02:06:00.065 --> 02:06:01.200
You will only be disappointed.

1417
02:06:01.870 --> 02:06:03.260
So tell me who you are.

1418
02:06:05.230 --> 02:06:06.230
My name is Sinon.

1419
02:06:07.220 --> 02:06:09.860
I am an old soldier who fought
under your father at Troy.

1420
02:06:11.460 --> 02:06:12.460
Did you know my father?

1421
02:06:12.900 --> 02:06:15.780
I'm already taking orders from him
longer than I'd like to admit.

1422
02:06:17.130 --> 02:06:18.130
Wait. he's alive?

1423
02:06:19.080 --> 02:06:20.080
He lives.

1424
02:06:21.990 --> 02:06:22.990
So where is he?

1425
02:06:23.580 --> 02:06:24.580
It's nearby.

1426
02:06:25.290 --> 02:06:27.480
He sent me forward to
I assessed the situation.

1427
02:06:29.305 --> 02:06:30.900
My mother won't believe it.

1428
02:06:31.055 --> 02:06:32.220
No. you can't tell her.

1429
02:06:33.380 --> 02:06:34.380
What. nothing?

1430
02:06:35.660 --> 02:06:36.660
Tell her that.

1431
02:06:38.140 --> 02:06:40.160
Tell her you've made up your mind
that it is time for her to remarry.

1432
02:06:42.300 --> 02:06:43.660
He doesn't have to test my mother.

1433
02:06:43.720 --> 02:06:44.720
How can he doubt her?

1434
02:06:44.860 --> 02:06:45.860
He has no doubts.

1435
02:06:46.440 --> 02:06:48.480
But he has every reason to
to forget about him.

1436
02:06:50.620 --> 02:06:51.920
Are there any loyal servants?

1437
02:06:53.160 --> 02:06:54.160
Some.

1438
02:06:55.140 --> 02:06:56.820
One of them is being shown here right now.

1439
02:06:58.650 --> 02:07:00.500
We must gather the suitors in the palace.

1440
02:07:01.670 --> 02:07:02.700
That's never a problem.

1441
02:07:03.660 --> 02:07:04.860
Do you have gifts for Menelaus?

1442
02:07:05.340 --> 02:07:06.340
Yes. on my ship.

1443
02:07:07.140 --> 02:07:08.140
Good.

1444
02:07:08.680 --> 02:07:09.680
Come back as a prince.

1445
02:07:10.300 --> 02:07:11.300
Call a feast.

1446
02:07:11.920 --> 02:07:12.920
I'll be there.

1447
02:07:14.110 --> 02:07:15.390
What are you going to do at that party?

1448
02:07:16.160 --> 02:07:17.160
I will beg.

1449
02:07:17.820 --> 02:07:19.580
The clearest view of a person is from below.

1450
02:07:21.880 --> 02:07:23.120
How many suitors are there?

1451
02:07:23.640 --> 02:07:24.640
He didn't.

1452
02:07:25.600 --> 02:07:28.440
If all his men are like
you. then... She has no men.

1453
02:07:29.520 --> 02:07:30.520
But is it just you?

1454
02:07:31.740 --> 02:07:32.740
And you.

1455
02:07:39.080 --> 02:07:40.120
Telemachus is back.

1456
02:07:40.360 --> 02:07:40.620
What?

1457
02:07:40.720 --> 02:07:41.720
Telemachus is back.

1458
02:07:42.265 --> 02:07:43.500
Who says that?

1459
02:07:43.865 --> 02:07:44.865
Everyone says that.

1460
02:07:45.600 --> 02:07:46.600
Where is Telemachus?

1461
02:07:47.160 --> 02:07:48.160
My queen!

1462
02:07:48.420 --> 02:07:49.460
He'll be here any minute.

1463
02:07:58.190 --> 02:07:59.190
It's true.

1464
02:08:01.890 --> 02:08:02.890
You are at home.

1465
02:08:04.055 --> 02:08:05.055
I'm back.

1466
02:08:05.775 --> 02:08:07.255
I thought we could celebrate tonight.

1467
02:08:08.070 --> 02:08:11.070
If we have anything left to celebrate at all.

1468
02:08:12.550 --> 02:08:13.550
Don't worry.

1469
02:08:14.330 --> 02:08:17.070
My valiant suitors shower us with gifts to honor your return.

1470
02:08:17.365 --> 02:08:18.930
I'm so glad you came back safe.

1471
02:08:30.100 --> 02:08:31.260
I like to see you on your feet.

1472
02:08:31.985 --> 02:08:33.825
It is high time we took you back to the palace.

1473
02:08:37.810 --> 02:08:39.250
What did you hear about your father?

1474
02:08:41.180 --> 02:08:42.180
Nothing.

1475
02:08:43.010 --> 02:08:46.300
Tales of the War. but no one knew what became of him after he left Troy.

1476
02:08:46.860 --> 02:08:47.860
I'm sorry. mom.

1477
02:08:49.310 --> 02:08:52.540
Everyone in Sparta is talking about the impending disaster.

1478
02:08:53.780 --> 02:08:57.580
A dark age brought by the people of the sea. breaking the law of Zeus.

1479
02:08:57.790 --> 02:08:58.880
Some stories are true.

1480
02:08:59.140 --> 02:09:00.680
Our civilization is collapsing.

1481
02:09:01.425 --> 02:09:04.225
Menelaus worries that we cannot raise an army with an empty throne.

1482
02:09:04.880 --> 02:09:05.920
So we came up with a plan.

1483
02:09:07.560 --> 02:09:08.560
What plan?

1484
02:09:11.010 --> 02:09:16.460
The only way to make suitors go away is to make a choice.

1485
02:09:20.490 --> 02:09:21.670
Do you want me to remarry?

1486
02:09:22.205 --> 02:09:24.760
If you remarry. the other suitors will leave

1487
02:09:24.761 --> 02:09:26.910
and then I only deal with
one of them.

1488
02:09:27.310 --> 02:09:28.310
I'm almost an adult.

1489
02:09:28.370 --> 02:09:31.190
I will tell the elders that I am
learned of Odysseus' death in Sparta.

1490
02:09:32.450 --> 02:09:35.310
Menelaus will support me and
they will allow me to take the throne.

1491
02:09:35.430 --> 02:09:38.890
So you renounce your father and I abandon mine
home and I'm going to live with one of these snakes.

1492
02:09:38.970 --> 02:09:39.970
Is that your plan?

1493
02:09:40.205 --> 02:09:41.325
Could you do better?

1494
02:09:43.975 --> 02:09:47.130
Lock the door. lock it
fire and burn those bastards.

1495
02:09:48.690 --> 02:09:52.130
Do you think if I remarry
will life go back to its old ways?

1496
02:09:53.400 --> 02:09:54.910
That world is gone.

1497
02:09:55.235 --> 02:09:58.110
And in this case they will not give up
power in your favor.

1498
02:09:58.770 --> 02:09:59.770
Not even in favor of Odysseus.

1499
02:09:59.810 --> 02:10:01.670
If he came back. he would have to kill her.

1500
02:10:02.310 --> 02:10:03.310
Just like you.

1501
02:10:04.270 --> 02:10:07.190
If I kill them. their families will claim
revenge.

1502
02:10:07.290 --> 02:10:08.290
They would expel me.

1503
02:10:09.580 --> 02:10:11.350
And without me the throne will be lost.

1504
02:10:11.390 --> 02:10:13.090
Because only a man can sit on it.

1505
02:10:14.844 --> 02:10:15.870
An empty throne?

1506
02:10:17.555 --> 02:10:20.370
I sit on that empty throne
twenty years!

1507
02:10:21.530 --> 02:10:24.295
My knowledge. my years
experience. that's all

1508
02:10:24.296 --> 02:10:26.551
nothing in comparison
with stubble on your chin.

1509
02:10:29.640 --> 02:10:30.640
Do you want peace?

1510
02:10:31.850 --> 02:10:32.850
Or do you want revenge?

1511
02:10:32.890 --> 02:10:33.930
I want a contradiction!

1512
02:10:37.360 --> 02:10:44.600
Sing. Muse. about the face. about the face.

1513
02:10:49.420 --> 02:11:01.290
about the fleet. war. toil.

1514
02:11:05.550 --> 02:11:12.380
Sing tidings of a man. a man

1515
02:11:16.990 --> 02:11:22.590
about an idea. about a trick.

1516
02:11:27.015 --> 02:11:35.880
You may go on in peace. Argos.

1517
02:11:59.140 --> 02:12:00.620
You should bury him up on the cliffs.

1518
02:12:03.110 --> 02:12:04.110
where did you meet

1519
02:12:13.130 --> 02:12:14.130
you are Odysseus.

1520
02:12:17.540 --> 02:12:18.540
You are my father.

1521
02:12:21.320 --> 02:12:22.340
I am a beggar.

1522
02:12:26.640 --> 02:12:34.640
And you are a good. beautiful son
Odyssey.

1523
02:12:36.660 --> 02:12:43.180
Which. when you finally meet.
he will be so proud.

1524
02:12:47.500 --> 02:12:49.740
Welcome home. stranger.

1525
02:12:53.510 --> 02:12:58.100
Because the darkness of victory
shrouds those who write legends.

1526
02:13:00.570 --> 02:13:03.040
And it makes us all
poets and blind beggars.

1527
02:13:10.660 --> 02:13:12.480
Accept the hospitality of Zeus.

1528
02:13:12.775 --> 02:13:14.560
Bring a stranger something to eat.

1529
02:13:15.180 --> 02:13:16.180
No. sir.

1530
02:13:16.550 --> 02:13:18.540
I'll just finish them off with one bullet.

1531
02:13:24.410 --> 02:13:26.850
I had to invite another one today
from these dirty lickers.

1532
02:13:27.030 --> 02:13:28.760
What about one beggar
more at this feast?

1533
02:13:47.140 --> 02:13:49.780
We must kill him before again
he will not gain his position among the elders.

1534
02:13:49.980 --> 02:13:50.980
How?

1535
02:14:07.810 --> 02:14:08.810
Provoke him.

1536
02:14:09.165 --> 02:14:10.730
Make him grab one of the weapons.

1537
02:14:15.530 --> 02:14:19.550
He's no longer the young puppy. Mr. Bape.
you have to come back tonight

1538
02:14:19.830 --> 02:14:20.830
or we could have stopped.

1539
02:14:22.180 --> 02:14:23.180
Hit it. old man.

1540
02:14:23.670 --> 02:14:24.670
Please.

1541
02:14:24.820 --> 02:14:25.950
I haven't eaten in days.

1542
02:14:25.970 --> 02:14:27.210
I told you. hit it!

1543
02:14:27.250 --> 02:14:30.110
You can't be generous with food that doesn't even
it's not yours.

1544
02:14:32.210 --> 02:14:33.610
There is no room in your bowl.

1545
02:14:33.975 --> 02:14:34.975
Yes. it is.

1546
02:14:40.700 --> 02:14:41.700
So it is.

1547
02:14:43.500 --> 02:14:44.500
Let him like it.

1548
02:14:49.010 --> 02:14:50.650
I assume you want something from me now.

1549
02:14:50.780 --> 02:14:51.780
Nope.

1550
02:14:52.060 --> 02:14:54.000
I have something for you.

1551
02:14:55.150 --> 02:14:56.190
Do you have something for me?

1552
02:14:57.580 --> 02:14:58.760
You have something for me!

1553
02:15:00.560 --> 02:15:06.740
What would such a dirty plate licker like
are you. could you have what I could want?

1554
02:15:08.080 --> 02:15:09.560
It's actually yours.

1555
02:15:15.500 --> 02:15:16.840
They asked me to return it to you.

1556
02:15:19.120 --> 02:15:20.120
That's not mine.

1557
02:15:22.120 --> 02:15:23.120
No?

1558
02:15:26.680 --> 02:15:27.680
Where did you come up with that?

1559
02:15:30.340 --> 02:15:32.060
Don't turn your back on me!

1560
02:15:37.410 --> 02:15:38.410
It's disrespectful.

1561
02:15:39.140 --> 02:15:40.570
You can't treat a beggar like that.

1562
02:15:40.650 --> 02:15:41.650
It is the law of Zeus.

1563
02:15:42.370 --> 02:15:43.370
Zeus' law.

1564
02:15:48.090 --> 02:15:49.090
Do you think he is a god?

1565
02:15:53.090 --> 02:15:54.380
Do you think he is a god in disguise?

1566
02:15:55.420 --> 02:15:56.420
Are you him?

1567
02:15:58.590 --> 02:15:59.590
are you a god

1568
02:16:00.820 --> 02:16:01.820
White alcohol?

1569
02:16:02.900 --> 02:16:03.900
Nope.

1570
02:16:04.920 --> 02:16:06.540
I am a veteran of the Trojan War.

1571
02:16:07.490 --> 02:16:09.280
A veteran of the Trojan War.

1572
02:16:12.260 --> 02:16:13.460
And what's your name. veteran?

1573
02:16:18.150 --> 02:16:19.150
Synod.

1574
02:16:22.700 --> 02:16:24.180
Does the name mean anything to you?

1575
02:16:25.320 --> 02:16:26.320
Nope.

1576
02:16:27.790 --> 02:16:31.520
I use it to honor the bravest
young man I have ever met.

1577
02:16:32.340 --> 02:16:33.340
Sinan?

1578
02:16:34.859 --> 02:16:36.120
I'm not your shepherd.

1579
02:16:39.069 --> 02:16:40.160
I don't remember that.

1580
02:16:40.185 --> 02:16:42.600
Yes. yes. he wanted him to take his place.

1581
02:16:43.345 --> 02:16:44.345
Where did you find this?

1582
02:16:45.239 --> 02:16:46.240
Where it will soon be.

1583
02:16:47.440 --> 02:16:48.440
And where is it?

1584
02:16:49.660 --> 02:16:50.660
Hades.

1585
02:16:54.280 --> 02:16:55.280
Enough!

1586
02:16:56.939 --> 02:16:58.240
The feast is over!

1587
02:17:02.639 --> 02:17:03.639
Collection.

1588
02:17:05.249 --> 02:17:06.249
She wasn't mine.

1589
02:17:15.179 --> 02:17:16.820
The Queen would like to speak with you.

1590
02:17:17.330 --> 02:17:19.459
Stay while everyone else
they will not remain in hell fire.

1591
02:18:10.659 --> 02:18:11.659
Hello. traveler.

1592
02:18:12.590 --> 02:18:13.590
My queen.

1593
02:18:14.435 --> 02:18:17.770
Melantha. leave your Clay
wash the stranger's feet.

1594
02:18:18.340 --> 02:18:19.370
This is not necessary.

1595
02:18:19.629 --> 02:18:23.010
My husband insisted
to honor guests as family.

1596
02:18:24.039 --> 02:18:25.690
Do you know Odysseus. my husband?

1597
02:18:26.290 --> 02:18:27.290
Of course.

1598
02:18:28.030 --> 02:18:29.030
From those songs?

1599
02:18:29.840 --> 02:18:31.030
I was in Troy. ma'am.

1600
02:18:32.139 --> 02:18:33.709
And those songs must have seemed silly to you.

1601
02:18:35.609 --> 02:18:36.609
They bring tears to my eyes.

1602
02:18:38.000 --> 02:18:39.000
Why?

1603
02:18:39.809 --> 02:18:40.809
For what was lost.

1604
02:18:41.650 --> 02:18:42.650
Those lives?

1605
02:18:43.670 --> 02:18:44.670
And those years.

1606
02:18:46.150 --> 02:18:47.150
Everything.

1607
02:18:55.089 --> 02:18:56.430
Did you know Odysseus in Troy?

1608
02:18:57.389 --> 02:18:58.389
He knew.

1609
02:18:59.525 --> 02:19:02.370
There was some detail
about how he dressed?

1610
02:19:02.450 --> 02:19:03.450
Something he was wearing?

1611
02:19:04.339 --> 02:19:05.670
He wore a strange clasp.

1612
02:19:06.530 --> 02:19:07.530
Strange?

1613
02:19:08.549 --> 02:19:11.090
Beautiful. but out of place.

1614
02:19:11.870 --> 02:19:12.870
Describe her.

1615
02:19:27.399 --> 02:19:28.440
I'll go get more water.

1616
02:19:33.489 --> 02:19:35.700
